          "text": [
            "<h3>Problem Overview</h3><p>This problem continues to build student expertise in working with unit rates to solve ratio problems of greater complexity. Students will be given a chance to solve situations using a variety of strategies for finding equivalent ratios. The strategies may include finding unit rates, making ratio tables, multiplying/dividing both quantities in a ratio (scaling) to find larger or smaller values as needed, and other informal strategies based on multiplicative reasoning. Also, students will us their ratio reasoning to make sense of converting units. </p>"
